title: Flow Meter
asset_description:
BCT 3/8x1/8 A

A clamp-on transducer that measures liquid flow through single use tubing (18-0102) by sound wave technology. The unit communicates to a Quattroflow pump.
intended_use: Intended for use at column chromatography during steps to measure flow rates.
calibration_description:
Semi-annual calibration by manufacturer (in Germany - unit needs to be shipped out for CAL) using water at ambient temp with C-Flex 374 [#23] (BCT 3/8 x 1/8A) tubing material.  Maximum flow rate is 10lpm, calibration at 1lpm (+/-5%), 5lpm (+/-3.4%) and 8lpm (+/- 3.3%). 

Three primary factors influence the accuracy of the meter: tubing material, the density of the medium and temperature of the liquid being measured. Therefore the unit must be calibrated to the specific tubing material and dimensions.
maintenance_justification_no: No preventive maintenance is required per manufacturer and/or vendor as there are no moving parts within the unit.
comments: Performance Qualification consisted of Flow Meter Verification at 1, 2, 5, 7 lpm for seven buffers and Quattroflow Pump Totalizer Verification at 1 and 7 lpm for WFI.  All acceptance criteria passed.

title: Quattroflow Pump with Flow Meter function
asset_description: Quaternary diaphragm pump with Single use pump chamber. This pump has Pendotech pressure sensor capability, and ability for communication with Emtec Bio-TT Flow Meter.
intended_use: With flow meter capability, it will be mostly for use in column chromatography. This pump can also be used in viral and ultra filtration steps. Because it will be used to determine flow rate and CVs flowed over the column, it is a relatively high impact unit in the MFG process.  Refer to specific batch record for appropriate process range at point of use.
calibration_justification_no: The Quattroflow pump utilizes the flow rate output from the Emtec Flow Meter (Asset #1658) which gets calibrated annually, thus the pump itself does not need calibration and it was not recommended  by the manufacturer.
maintenance_justification_no:
No scheduled maintenance is required per manufacturer.  It was recommended that the Shaft-Bearing Cap Unit gets replaced if liquid infiltrates it and/or a leak is observed.  

Single-Use pump chambers shall be thrown out after each use (filtrations) or dedicated to a column and used for a campaign.
comments: Performance Qualification consisted of Flow Meter Asset #1658  Verification at 1, 2, 5, 7 lpm for seven buffers and Quattroflow Pump Totalizer Verification at 1 and 7 lpm for WFI.  All acceptance criteria passed.

title: Quattroflow Pump
asset_description: Quatrenary pump with single use pump chamber and pendotech pressure shutoff.
intended_use: For use in chromatography, VF and UF/DF steps. High impact to the process.
process_range: Flow cabability: 0.02-27L/min, processes have varying flow rates.  Pressure: up to 40 psi.
calibration_justification_no: Pump does not require calibration because the operator will be collecting the buffers and confirming the weight using a calibrated scale, therefore not relying on flow rate or speed on the pump.  When flow rate is required, it will be taken with a graduated cylinder and calibrated timer per batch record.
maintenance_justification_no:
No scheduled maintenance is required per manufacturer.  It was recommended that the Shaft-Bearing Cap Unit gets replaced if liquid infiltrates it and/or a leak is observed.  

Single-Use pump chambers shall be thrown out after each use (filtrations) or dedicated to a column and used for a campaign.

title: Quattroflow Pump
asset_description: Quatrenary pump with single use pump chamber and pendotech pressure shutoff.
intended_use: For use column chromatography or in VF and UF/DF steps. High impact to the process.
process_range: Flow capability: 0.02 - 27 LPM with varying process ranges. Pressure limit set to 40 psi
calibration_justification_no: Pump does not require calibration because the operator will be collecting the buffers and confirming the weight using a calibrated scale, therefore not relying on flow rate or speed on the pump. When the flow rate is required, it will be taken with a graduated cylinder and a calibrated timer per batch record.
maintenance_justification_no:
No scheduled maintenance is required per manufacturer.  It was recommended that the Shaft-Bearing Cap Unit gets replaced if liquid infiltrates it and/or a leak is observed.  

Single-Use pump chambers shall be thrown out after each use (filtrations) or dedicated to a column and used for a campaign.

title: Vi-Cell Cell Counter
asset_description: Cell counter and cell viability analyzer
intended_use: Perform cell counting and cell viability measurements
calibration_description:
- Measure power supply on J2 of the power supply, record values
- verify the optics and sample cell are clean from dust or blemishes
- verify the average light intensity is within 205+/-15
- verify front panel LED
- verify carousel alignment.  Ensure sample cup stops as close as possible within center of the cup sensing zone in all positions. 
-verify aspiration tube length.  Ensure aspiration tubing reaches the bottom of the cup in all positions
- Verify sipper arm alignment.  Ensure sipper arm metal portion is centered in the guide hole as it goes down. 
- verify total count / ml (concentration) is within 10% of assay value during instrument performance test
maintenance_description:
1. Clean and inspect the chassis to ensure a good and clean condition.
2. Inspect the video and computer cables to ensure they are connected and in good
condition.
3. Check tubing for deterioration or kinks.
4. Replace the syringe (once each year) as part of the annual certification.
5. Verify the syringe connection (top) to the distribution valve is finger tight.
6. Verify the syringe lock is rotated full left and locked in place.
7. Ensure syringe plunger bottom screw is tight.
8. Verify the distribution valve fittings are tight.
comments: Vendor provided IOQ/V-check was performed successfully

title: 1871: LyoStar 3
calibration_description: Calibration required for 32 product temperature probes, 1 condenser thermocouple probe, 1 interstage thermocouple probe, and vacuum-level sensors.
maintenance_description:
Quarterly:
1. Vacuum leak rate test
2. Function test

Annual:
1. Check static pressure in refrigeration system. Compare obtained readings to the information on the refrigeration charge nameplates. Check for refrigerant leaks if the indicated pressure has deviated more than 10 psig.
2. Check fluid level of refrigeration system. Check refrigeration system piping and components for fluid leaks.
3. Check the fluid level of the heat-transfer system. Check heat-transfer system piping and components for fluid leaks.
4. Lubricate all motors that require lubrication.
5. Inspect the product chamber and condenser door gaskets for age cracks, worn spots and/or minor cuts. Replace as needed.
6. Inspect all rubber vacuum connections utilized for vacuum-level sensor connections, vacuum bleed and vacuum break connections. Check for age cracks, worn spots or minor cuts. Grease the inside diameter of vacuum tubes with vacuum grease and re-install.

title: Universal Tank Switching System for LN2
asset_description: The Pacer TSH Tank Switching System is a universal tank switching system for LN2. It can be used with any manufacturers’ cryo-freezers. The universal tank system switch between an empty LN2 tank and the secondary LN2 tank, the universal tank switcher monitors the flow of LN2 through the use of a thermistor (thermal resistor).
intended_use: When the thermistors detect that LN2 is no longer flowing, the tank switcher switches to an alternate supply.

title: Em-tec Flow Meter
asset_description: Clamp-on transducer that measures liquid flow through single use tubing via sound wave technology. The unit is part of a system with the Quattfoflow pump.
intended_use: Measurement of flow rate during column chromatography steps
calibration_description:
Semi-annual calibration by manufacturer (in Germany - unit needs to be shipped out for CAL) using water at ambient temp with C-Flex 374 [#23] (BCT 3/8 x 1/8A) tubing material. Maximum flow rate is 10LPM, calibration at 1LPM (+/- 5%), 5LPM (+/- 3.4%) and 8LPM (+/- 3.3%).

Accuracy is determined based on tubing material, density of liquid, and temperature of the liquid.
maintenance_justification_no: No preventative maintenance is required per manufacturer and vendor as there are no moving parts within the unit.
